data.chText: 他在自己的绘画艺术中打破了科学的直线透视法规律。
data.enText: In his art he broke the laws of scientific linear perspective.

data.chText: 学生不会总是顺着一条直线进步。
data.enText: Students do not always progress in a linear fashion.

data.enText: She abandoned the linearity of the conventional novel.

value.def: A linear process or development is one in which something changes or progresses straight from one stage to another, and has a starting point and an ending point.

example.ex: Her novel subverts the conventions of linear narrative. It has no neat chronology and no tidy denouement.
example.tran: 她的小说颠覆了线性叙事的传统，没有清晰的时间线索，也没有简单明了的结局。

example.ex: ...the linear view of time, with the idea that the past is moving into the present and the present into the future.
example.tran: 线性的时间观，认为过去通向现在，现在通向未来。

value.def: A linear shape or form consists of straight lines.

example.ex: ...the sharp, linear designs of the Seventies and Eighties.
example.tran: 七八十年代轮廓清晰的线条设计

value.def: Linear movement or force occurs in a straight line rather than in a curve.
value.tran: （运动或力）成一直线的，沿直线的
